"{\"description\":\"We have a fantastic opportunity for someone looking to develop their Commercial career path. As a Commercial Manager, you will provide pre and post-contract commercial management for the Maintenance Delivery Units in the Routes. The role is varied across pre-contract procurement, post-contract administration, financial review, and regular meetings with key suppliers. Essential requirements include extensive experience in commercial management, demonstrable relevant experience, good negotiation skills, and a good understanding of NR Suite and construction industry forms of contract. Desirable qualifications include being educated to degree standard, membership of a relevant professional institute, and awareness of industry issues.\",\"howToApply\":\"Applicants should demonstrate their personal commitment to safety in their application. All prospective candidates offered a conditional role will be required to undergo and pass a drugs and alcohol test. A career with Network Rail offers a structured pay framework, 28 days holiday, contributory pension schemes, and a range of benefits. Network Rail offers flexible working and accessibility support, and reasonable adjustments/modifications can be requested.\",\"aboutTheRole\":{\"essential\":[\"Extensive experience in commercial management.\",\"Demonstrable relevant experience\",\"Good understanding of NR Suite and construction industry forms of contract\",\"Good understanding of the construction/railway industry\",\"Good negotiation skills\"],\"desirable\":[\"Educated to degree standard in related subject\",\"Membership of a relevant professional institute, chartered status\",\"Awareness of industry issues\"],\"keyAccountabilities\":[\"Provide pre and post-contract commercial management for the Maintenance Delivery Units in the Routes.\",\"Pre-contract procurement, post-contract administration, financial review, and regular meetings with key suppliers.\"]},\"line-6\":\"About Network Rail\"}"